The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 February is 37,357 (4,323.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 31 January, there were 2,086 new confirmed cases (241.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 January, there were 2,840 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 27% (754 fewer cases).
